"{\"uid\": \"nationaltribune.com.au-anatomy-of-a-wave-what-makes-the-olympic-surf-break-at-teahupo-o-unique-and-so-challenging\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"As the Olympics get going in earnest this week, not everyone's attention is focused on host city Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 97, \"end\": 102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999998834650111, \"rank\": 1.1653514643765623e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3, \"to\": 15}, {\"ngram\": \"earnest\", \"from\": 29, \"to\": 36}, {\"ngram\": \"not everyone's attention\", \"from\": 48, \"to\": 72}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surf fans are heading to Tahiti, half a world away in French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 104, \"to\": 175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9960207649649105, \"rank\": 0.0039951326065843845, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 165, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9275893760723684, \"rank\": 0.07806323120476796, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Surf fans\", \"from\": 104, \"to\": 113}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Shand Honorary Senior Lecturer, Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, University of Auckland, Waipapa Taumata Rau Why?\", \"from\": 177, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 177, \"end\": 186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Department\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"Civil and Environmental Engineering\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 262}, {\"ngram\": \"University\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 274}, {\"ngram\": \"Auckland\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 286}, {\"ngram\": \"Waipapa Taumata Rau\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 307}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, apart from the French coast resembling a lake at this time of year, on the south-west coast of Tahiti Iti is a wave unlike any other on the planet: Teahupo'o, which translates somewhat ominously as \\\"place of skulls\\\".\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 336, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9965653737785576, \"rank\": 0.0030123565875588903, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lake\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"this time\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"year\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 387}, {\"ngram\": \"the south-west coast\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"Tahiti\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"Iti\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 426}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 467}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"skulls\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave is unique in the way it breaks.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wave\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lower part of the wave appears to drop away below sea level, with the top half folding over dramatically to create an almost cartoonishly perfect form.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lower part\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 606}, {\"ngram\": \"sea level\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"the top half\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"an almost cartoonishly perfect form\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is both the weight of water in the plunging lip and the risk of injury or death for a surfer in the wrong position that make this one of the world's heaviest waves (in both senses of the word).\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"the plunging lip\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 787}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"a surfer\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"the wrong position\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 854}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's heaviest waves\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"both senses\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 919}, {\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To understand why the wave breaks like this, we need to start withbathymetry: the shape of the seabed that influences waves as they approach the shore.\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"withbathymetry\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"the shape\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"the seabed\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"the shore\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Teahupo'o, acombination of factorscomes into play.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1140, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"acombination\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"factorscomes\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves arriving at Teahupo'o generally originate from intense \\\"roaring forties\\\" storm systems south of New Zealand.\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1244, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\", \"score\": 0.5446388060416224, \"rank\": 0.4990404841439279, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Waves\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"intense \\\"roaring forties\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"storm systems\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the waves reach Tahiti they have become ordered swell, with wave heights of two to five metres and periods of 14 to 20 seconds between successive waves.\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9960207649649105, \"rank\": 0.0039951326065843845, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"wave heights\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"two to five metres\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"periods\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"14 to 20 seconds\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"successive waves\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These types of long-period waves normally start interacting with the seabed at depths of around 200 metres.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These types\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"long-period waves\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"the seabed\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"depths\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"around 200 metres\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On most coasts, this depth would occur up to several kilometres offshore.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most coasts\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"this depth\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"several kilometres\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But at Teahupo'o, it is much closer, just a couple of hundred metres.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just a couple of hundred metres\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This rapid change in depth forces the wave to \\\"shoal\\\" very quickly - the wave speed slows, the distance between waves compresses and the wave height increases.\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1835, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This rapid change\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"depth forces\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1709}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1718}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave speed\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave height increases\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The change is so abrupt that the wave is still very linear - it has not had time to develop the peaked crest and flat trough (the lowest part of the wave) typical of waves in shallow water.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The change\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1874}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"the peaked crest\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"flat trough\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"the lowest part\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 1990}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"shallow water\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves breaking on this type of steep slope would typically collapse, breaking from the middle of the wave and creating an unsurfable mess.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2166, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Waves\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"this type\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"steep slope\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2070}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2121}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2133}, {\"ngram\": \"an unsurfable mess\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this does not happen.\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At around ten metres' depth, a flatter shelf in the reef allows the wave to stabilise and \\\"stand up\\\" with a steep front face, before finally breaking as the reef rises again.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"around ten metres' depth\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"a flatter shelf\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"a steep front face\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2318}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And break it does.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to the linearity, there is far more water in the crest (the part above water) then most waves, and a deeper trough in front.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the linearity\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"far more water\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2436}, {\"ngram\": \"the crest\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2449}, {\"ngram\": \"the part\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"most waves\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"a deeper trough\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2509}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes for the characteristic below-sea-level break at Teahupo'o, with the overturning lip being half the wave height, and a jet of compressed air forced out of the wave's barrel after breaking.\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sea-level\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2570}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2589}, {\"ngram\": \"the overturning lip\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2615}, {\"ngram\": \"half the wave height\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"a jet\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2653}, {\"ngram\": \"compressed air\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave's barrel\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The larger the wave, the closer to the steep offshore ramp it breaks, and the more extreme the plunging.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The larger the wave\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"the steep offshore ramp\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"the more extreme the plunging\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A range of other unique features contribute to the way the wave breaks at Teahupo'o - and what makes it so challenging as a surfing wave.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A range\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"other unique features\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2881}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2890}, {\"ngram\": \"a surfing wave\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 2963}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A deep channel runs alongside the shallow reef shelf.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A deep channel runs\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"the shallow reef shelf\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave does not break in this deeper area, allowing it to peel - to break in one direction (in this case towards the left looking towards the shore) - and enabling surfers to ride the wave before it finally closes out onto shallow reef.\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3258, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wave\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3028}, {\"ngram\": \"this deeper area\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3063}, {\"ngram\": \"one direction\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3112}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"the shore\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3169}, {\"ngram\": \"surfers\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3210}, {\"ngram\": \"shallow reef\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A part of the shallow reef platform extends offshore, into the reef pass.\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A part\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3266}, {\"ngram\": \"the shallow reef platform\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3295}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef pass\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This shallow area bends and focuses wave energy from the wider, deeper part of the wave back into the breaking wave.\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This shallow area bends\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3357}, {\"ngram\": \"wave energy\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3381}, {\"ngram\": \"the wider, deeper part\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3409}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3413, \"to\": 3421}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaking wave\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This happens particularly on more westerly orientated swells, increasing the intensity of breaking.\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more westerly orientated swells\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3511}, {\"ngram\": \"the intensity\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3537}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as this, the Teahupo'o wave breaks in a direction nearly opposite to the prevailing trade winds, keeping the wave face smooth.\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a direction\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3609}, {\"ngram\": \"the prevailing trade winds\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3655}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"face\", \"from\": 3674, \"to\": 3678}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A low tidal range also limits the times the reef is too deep or too shallow to surf.\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A low tidal range\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3705}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3727}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"surf\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the wave is near the Passa Hava'e reef pass, which helps the wave's focusing and breaking.\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"score\": 0.9999999954807208, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Passa\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3785}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3842}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3866}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But because it is not right in the pass, the wave is not affected by high tidal or wave-induced currents.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3973, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pass\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3907}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3917}, {\"ngram\": \"high tidal or wave-induced currents\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 3972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New-generation wave models that simulate individual waves, rather than just average energy density, provide insight into what creates a surf break such as Teahupo'o (see figure below).\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4159, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"New-generation wave models\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4001}, {\"ngram\": \"individual waves\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4032}, {\"ngram\": \"just average energy density\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4073}, {\"ngram\": \"insight\", \"from\": 4083, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"a surf break\", \"from\": 4109, \"to\": 4121}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 4130, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"figure\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These models provide insight into what happens as waves shoal and refract (bend and focus) over the seabed as they approach break point.\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4296, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These models\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4172}, {\"ngram\": \"insight\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4188}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4215}, {\"ngram\": \"the seabed\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4266}, {